text: Linköpings FC is an association football club in the town of Linköping in Sweden. it was established in 2003 when the Kenty DFF women's association football club decided to merge with the ice hockey club Linköpings HC under the new name Linköpings FC. The club won the Swedish women's association football national championship of 2009. ==References== ==Other websites== * Official website Category:2003 establishments in Sweden Category:Linköping Category:Swedish football clubs
